                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>The letters are engraved in broad, rounded strokes (partly the result of weathering) and have a regular form. K has arms that do not quite reach to the top and bottom of the letter; E has strokes of equal length; A has broken bar. The text is either Latin or a mixture or Latin and Greek, given the presence of L in the second line.</p>
